		----------------------------
		The LLg package set - V 1.07
	        ----------------------------
		       For PERL5.001m
	               --------------


LLg is a set of PERL packages for automating the process of developping
recursive descent parsers.

This set includes packages for implementing lexical and syntactical
analysers. With LLg it's very easy to develop parsers for small
languages. LLg is documented, and provided with some examples.

LLg comprises two major packages :
1. Lex.pm - Generator of lexical analyzers 
2. LLg.pm - Generator of parsers for CF grammars

It's an alpha version so use LLg and Lex just for explorations and
experimentations.

The LLg parser generator is available in:

	ftp://www.eurolang.fr/pub/perl

